Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a distributed algorithm for finding Euler circuits in large graphs partitioned across distributed machines. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper deals with the classic problem of finding Euler circuits in graphs and proposes a novel partition-centric algorithm for the same. 
3. cs.NE (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper mentions the use of Euler circuits in the Internet of Things, which falls under the purview of networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.Distributed - The paper proposes a distributed algorithm for finding Euler circuits in large graphs, which falls under the domain of distributed computing. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper analyzes the complexity of the proposed algorithm and identifies memory bottlenecks, which falls under the domain of computational complexity.
